## Q4. Total computing time

This is a fair criticism, raised independently by all three reviewers. Table 1
isolates the M-step because that is where the two algorithms differ
asymptotically --- the E-step is $\mathcal{O}(np)$ for both --- but reporting
only the component we improve is not the right way to present a computational
claim.

\rev{Revision: we now report end-to-end wall-clock time for every method in
every experiment (simulations and real data), together with the hardware
specification, in a new Table 9. Table 1 is retained as a decomposition, with
the text amended to state clearly that the $74$--$106\times$ figure refers to
the M-step alone and that the end-to-end factor is smaller.}
\rev{[TODO: total timings for Nash, mr.ash, Lasso, Enet, Ridge, XGBoost, MLP,
ipf-Lasso across SNP500 / Airpassenger / GSE40279 / TCGA; CPU model, core count,
