## Minor comments

**M1. Undefined symbols.** \rev{We have added a notation table (new Appendix
A.0) and defined at first use every symbol flagged, together with
$\omega$, $s_j^2$, $V_{q_{b_j}}$, $L_{jm}$, $\bar r_j$ and $\Sigma_j$.}

**M2. $P$ vs $p$.** These denote the same quantity. \rev{All occurrences are now
$p$; the products in Eqs. (7) and (12) have been corrected.}

**M3. Is prediction based on $\hat\beta$ or $\bar b$?** Predictions use the
posterior mean of the regression coefficients, $\bar\beta$, which is the
Bayes-optimal point predictor under squared error; $\bar b$ is the posterior
mean of the latent layer and is not the predictive coefficient. The reviewer has
correctly caught an inconsistency: Algorithm 1 returns $\bar b$, and Appendix
B.1 refers to $\hat\beta$. \rev{Algorithm 1 now returns $(\bar\beta, \bar b,
\hat\theta, \sigma^2)$, and Appendix B.1 states that RMSE is computed as
$\|y_{\text{test}} - X_{\text{test}}\bar\beta\|_2/\sqrt{n}$. We have verified
that the released implementation uses $\bar\beta$; the reported numbers are
unaffected.}

